Adding `direction: rtl` to your `&lt;ol&gt;` should do the trick. This changes the text direction from left (default) to right therefore the scrollbar starts from the right side.

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-css --&gt;

    ol {
      list-style: none;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      max-width: 200px;
      height: 50px;
      overflow-x: scroll;
      overflow-y: hidden;
      white-space: nowrap;
      direction: rtl;
    }

     li {
       display: inline-block;
     }

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;ol&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Lorem ipsum.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Nemo, atque?&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Dicta, perspiciatis!&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Voluptate, fugit!&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Atque, eligendi.&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Voluptate, in!&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Est, a!&lt;/li&gt;
      &lt;li&gt;Dolorem, quis.&lt;/li&gt;
    &lt;/ol&gt;

